  "prompt": "If somebody is smoking weed around me, is it possible to get high off of second hand smoke?",
  "response": "It is possible to experience some effects from secondhand marijuana smoke, especially in an enclosed or poorly ventilated space, but the likelihood of getting significantly high from secondhand exposure is generally low. The concentration of THC (the psychoactive compound in marijuana) in secondhand smoke is much lower than in directly inhaled smoke, and the exposure is typically less intense.\n\nHowever, factors such as the proximity to the smoker, the duration of exposure, the potency of the marijuana, and the ventilation of the space can influence whether you might feel any effects. Some people report mild symptoms like lightheadedness, relaxation, or altered perception after prolonged exposure in an enclosed area.\n\nIf you're concerned about secondhand exposure, it's a good idea to move to a well-ventilated area or ask the person to smoke elsewhere.",
